TY  - JOUR
AU  - Deb, Rahul
AU  - Kitamura, Yuichi
AU  - Quah, John K H
AU  - Stoye, Jörg
T1  - Revealed Price Preference: Theory and Empirical Analysis
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdac041
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 90
IS  - 2
SP  - 707
EP  - 743
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - To determine the welfare implications of price changes in demand data, we introduce a revealed preference relation over prices. We show that the absence of cycles in this relation characterizes a consumer who trades off the utility of consumption against the disutility of expenditure. Our model can be applied whenever a consumer’s demand over a strict subset of all available goods is being analysed; it can also be extended to settings with discrete goods and non-linear prices. To illustrate its use, we apply our model to a single-agent data set and to a data set with repeated cross-sections. We develop a novel test of linear hypotheses on partially identified parameters to estimate the proportion of the population who are revealed better off due to a price change in the latter application. This new technique can be used for non-parametric counterfactual analysis more broadly.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdac041
ER  - 



