TY  - JOUR
AU  - Kolb, Aaron
AU  - Madsen, Erik
T1  - Under Suspicion: Trust Dynamics with Secret Undermining
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdac034
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 90
IS  - 2
SP  - 912
EP  - 947
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We study how an organization should dynamically screen an agent of uncertain loyalty whom it suspects of committing damaging acts of undermining. The organization controls the stakes of the relationship, while the agent strategically times undermining, which can occur repeatedly and is detected only stochastically. The optimal commitment stakes policy exhibits both discreteness and gradualism, with distinct “untrusted” and “trusted” phases featuring gradually rising stakes during the untrusted phase and a discrete gap in stakes between phases. This policy is also the equilibrium outcome when the organization cannot commit, and the agent’s equilibrium undermining policy exhibits variable, non-monotonic intensity.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdac034
ER  - 



