TY  - JOUR
AU  - Pycia, Marek
AU  - Yenmez, M Bumin
T1  - Matching with Externalities
PY  - 2023
Y1  - 2023/03/01
DO  - 10.1093/restud/rdac032
JO  - The Review of Economic Studies
JA  - Rev Econ Stud
VL  - 90
IS  - 2
SP  - 948
EP  - 974
SN  - 0034-6527
AB  - We incorporate externalities into the stable matching theory of two-sided markets. Extending the classical substitutes condition to markets with externalities, we establish that stable matchings exist when agent choices satisfy substitutability. We show that substitutability is a necessary condition for the existence of a stable matching in a maximal-domain sense and provide a characterization of substitutable choice functions. In addition, we extend the standard insights of matching theory, like the existence of side-optimal stable matchings and the deferred acceptance algorithm, to settings with externalities even though the standard fixed-point techniques do not apply.
Y2  - 3/25/2024
UR  - https://doi.org/10.1093/restud/rdac032
ER  - 



